choices.text: You are given a string $s$ consisting only of upper case letters A and B. For an integer $k$, a pair of indices $i$ and $j$ ($1 \le i<j \le n$) is called a $k$-inversion if and only if $s[i] = \textbf{B}$, $s[j] = \textbf{A}$ and $j-i = k$. Consider the string BABA. It has two $1$-inversions and one $3$-inversion. It has no $2$-inversions. For each $k$ between $1$ and $n-1$ (inclusive), print the number of $k$-inversions in the string $s$.
